# Cambio Card Game

Cambio is a browser-based version of the memory card game where players try to
finish with the lowest-value hand. The game mixes luck, memory, and timing:
players memorize some of their cards, draw from the deck or discard pile, swap
cards, use special-card abilities, and try to eliminate matching cards when they
know what is on the table.

Live site: https://cambiogame.com

## Features

- Real-time multiplayer rooms over FastAPI WebSockets.
- Shareable room links such as `/join/ABC123`.
- Configurable starting hand size and deck count.
- Optional 60-second turn timer to prevent AFK turns from freezing a room.
- Single-player practice mode with a basic AI opponent.
- Mobile-friendly table layout with opponent hands, deck/discard, and your hand.
- Grace-period scoring after Cambio is called.
- Stale-room cleanup to keep server memory usage low.

## Tech Stack

- Backend: Python, FastAPI, Pydantic, WebSockets.
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript.
- Tests: pytest for backend game and room-manager behavior.

## Project Structure

- `Backend/backend.py`: FastAPI app, REST endpoints, WebSocket handler, room
  manager, scoring, cleanup, timers, and bot behavior.
- `Backend/test_*.py`: Backend tests for deck logic, room management, cleanup,
  scoring, and win-condition edge cases.
- `Frontend/index.html`: Main app markup and CSS.
- `Frontend/bridge.js`: Browser-side state bridge for API calls, WebSocket
  events, rendering, animations, and lobby actions.
- `Frontend/instructions.html`: Player-facing rules page.
- `Frontend/rules.pdf`: Downloadable rules reference.
- `GAME_MECHANICS_REFERENCE.md`: Notes for game rules and implementation.

## Local Development

Install backend dependencies:

```bash
python3 -m pip install -r Backend/requirements.txt
```

Run the backend and static frontend:

```bash
python3 -m uvicorn Backend.backend:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Run tests:

```bash
python3 -m pytest Backend
```

## Room Cleanup Policy

Rooms are stored in memory, so cleanup is intentionally conservative with RAM:

- Bot-only or abandoned bot rooms close after 5 minutes.
- Playing rooms with no connected human players close after 10 minutes.
- Playing rooms with connected humans close after 20 minutes of inactivity.
- Waiting rooms with no connected humans close after 15 minutes.
- Waiting rooms with connected humans close after 45 minutes.
- Finished rooms close after 10 minutes.

The cleanup task runs once per minute.

