## Lessons Learned

This project was a practical way to connect Python backend code with a browser
frontend through WebSockets. The most useful lessons were around keeping server
state authoritative, validating every gameplay action on the backend, designing
cleanup for an in-memory room system, and reviewing AI-generated code carefully
before shipping it.
